        "body": "I realized that a vanilla Rails 6.0.0 app consumes much memory than the previous version for handling each request.\r\n\r\nHere's what I did for measuring the memory usage for a simple action that returns a \"200 OK\" HEAD response.\r\n\r\n`% rails new rails6_app --skip-spring --skip-bootsnap`\r\n\r\n`% rails g controller top index`\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n# app/controllers/top_controller.rb\r\n@@ -1,4 +1,5 @@\r\n class TopController < ApplicationController\r\n   def index\r\n+    head :ok\r\n   end\r\n end\r\n```\r\n\r\n* Bundle `memory_profiler` gem\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n# app/controllers/application_controller.rb\r\n class ApplicationController < ActionController::Base\r\n+  def process_action(*)\r\n+    MemoryProfiler.report { super }.pretty_print(retained_strings: 0, allocated_strings: 0, detailed_report: false)\r\n+  end\r\n end\r\n```\r\n\r\n`% curl http://localhost:3000/top/index`\r\n\r\nAnd here are the results from the Rails 6.0.0 app.\r\n\r\n* Rails 6.0.0 results\r\n```\r\nTotal allocated: 33819 bytes (267 objects)\r\nTotal retained:  10776 bytes (56 objects)\r\n\r\nTotal allocated: 33819 bytes (267 objects)\r\nTotal retained:  10736 bytes (55 objects)\r\n\r\nTotal allocated: 33859 bytes (268 objects)\r\nTotal retained:  10736 bytes (55 objects)\r\n\r\nTotal allocated: 33313 bytes (264 objects)\r\nTotal retained:  10046 bytes (51 objects)\r\n\r\nTotal allocated: 33043 bytes (262 objects)\r\nTotal retained:  9920 bytes (49 objects)\r\n\r\nTotal allocated: 33353 bytes (265 objects)\r\nTotal retained:  10006 bytes (50 objects)\r\n```\r\n\r\nNext, I created exactly the same app on Rails version 5.2.3, and here are the results.\r\n\r\n\r\n* Rails 5.2 results\r\n```\r\nTotal allocated: 25406 bytes (247 objects)\r\nTotal retained:  6816 bytes (52 objects)\r\n\r\nTotal allocated: 25446 bytes (248 objects)\r\nTotal retained:  6816 bytes (52 objects)\r\n\r\nTotal allocated: 25406 bytes (247 objects)\r\nTotal retained:  6816 bytes (52 objects)\r\n\r\nTotal allocated: 25406 bytes (247 objects)\r\nTotal retained:  6816 bytes (52 objects)\r\n\r\nTotal allocated: 25446 bytes (248 objects)\r\nTotal retained:  6816 bytes (52 objects)\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou see, Rails 6.0.0 consumes 30% more memory than 5.2.3.\r\n\r\nI investigated a little bit deeper and found that the culprit was a `before_action` added via ActionText::Engine. https://github.com/rails/rails/blob/7dfd9d2387e3253f3abd85f7699ca44c338dc77f/actiontext/lib/action_text/engine.rb#L50\r\n\r\n\r\nIn fact, with this simple one-line deletion,\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n# .../gems/actiontext-6.0.0/lib/action_text/engine.rb\r\n@@ -47,7 +47,6 @@ module ActionText\r\n       end\r\n\r\n       ActiveSupport.on_load(:action_controller_base) do\r\n-        before_action { ActionText::Content.renderer = ApplicationController.renderer.new(request.env) }\r\n       end\r\n     end\r\n   end\r\n```\r\n\r\nthe Rails 6.0.0 app now responds with almost the same memory consumption as the 5.2.3 app.\r\n\r\n* Rails 6.0.0 with the patch results\r\n```\r\nTotal allocated: 25664 bytes (249 objects)\r\nTotal retained:  6856 bytes (53 objects)\r\n\r\nTotal allocated: 25664 bytes (249 objects)\r\nTotal retained:  6816 bytes (52 objects)\r\n\r\nTotal allocated: 24848 bytes (243 objects)\r\nTotal retained:  6000 bytes (46 objects)\r\n\r\nTotal allocated: 24848 bytes (243 objects)\r\nTotal retained:  6000 bytes (46 objects)\r\n\r\nTotal allocated: 25198 bytes (247 objects)\r\nTotal retained:  6086 bytes (47 objects)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe line I deleted was a `before_action` hook that instantiates a renderer for Action Text. This hook runs before every action in every controller even if the action does not use Action Text feature.\r\nAnd there's no way we can skip this hook because the hook has no name.\r\n\r\nI did not attach a patch because I'm not very much familiar with Action Text code base, but I guess there can be some approaches for fixing this issue. Maybe Action Text should instantiate the renderer on demand.\r\n\r\nAnd, for those of you who are running your apps on Rails 6.0.0, the only way that you can avoid this performance regression for now is to stop requiring `action_text/railtie` by doing something like this.\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n# config/application.rb\r\n@@ -1,6 +1,23 @@\r\n require_relative 'boot'\r\n\r\n-require 'rails/all'\r\n+%w(\r\n+  active_record/railtie\r\n+  active_storage/engine\r\n+  action_controller/railtie\r\n+  action_view/railtie\r\n+  action_mailer/railtie\r\n+  active_job/railtie\r\n+  action_cable/engine\r\n+  action_mailbox/engine\r\n+  rails/test_unit/railtie\r\n+  sprockets/railtie\r\n+).each do |railtie|\r\n+  begin\r\n+    require railtie\r\n+  rescue LoadError\r\n+  end\r\n+end\r\n```"
      },
