        "author_association": "MEMBER",
        "body": "Can’t say I recognize the need this is addressing. Is it possible to do as a gem?\n\n> On Aug 14, 2019, at 21:39, Jim Jones <notifications@github.com> wrote:\n> \n> Changed the rendering hints format.\n> \n> \n> \n> Start/end comments are now begin/end comments.\n> \n> There's now a render ID that prefixes each begin/end comment making it easier to scan for begin/end pairs. There are periods spacers for the begin/end comments to signify when a partial is nested and being rendered by a parent partial.\n> \n> @dhh Thoughts on the concept and the begin/end hint format?\n> \n> —\n> You are receiving this because you were mentioned.\n> Reply to this email directly, view it on GitHub, or mute the thread.\n"
