        "pull_request": {
          "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/pulls/36873",
          "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/36873",
          "diff_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/36873.diff",
          "patch_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/36873.patch"
        },
        "body": "Previously, every time we ran tests in parallel we would load the schema for all _N_ databases, and then drop them at the end of testing.\r\n\r\nNow that we have the ability to sync DBs with the schema file exactly using metadata and a SHA, we can instead only load the schemas when they change. In order for this to work we no longer drop the databases at the end of the tests. If the schema is in sync, we truncate the tables to ensure we start with an empty DB.\r\n\r\nI believe this will make setup fast enough to close https://github.com/rails/rails/issues/36807\r\n\r\nBuilds on #36870, obsoletes #36826"
      },
