        "author_association": "MEMBER",
        "body": "Yes, I do think that we're better off saying \"if you use a Rails framework, you're getting all of Active Support\". That's a clear expectation. I fully accept that there'll be people who don't like that approach, but at least it's clear.\r\n\r\nThe only part that I do think is fair is that for Active Support ITSELF to be piecemeal, as far as that goes. So that you could require, say, the TZ extensions, and you'd only get a partial amount of AS. But to be honest, that optimization is pretty low my list of priorities. I'd not be willing to give up very much to allow piecemeal inclusion of Active Support extensions to get it."
