        "author_association": "MEMBER",
        "body": "I appreciate the deep dive, but I disagree with the premise. First of all, I don't consider Active Support's extensions to be pollution, but rather beautification 😄. Active Support offers a Rails-tinted dialect of Ruby, which not only makes the language more pleasant for Rails programmers, but strikes to the very essence of why I love Ruby. That this is possible!\r\n\r\nSo in fact, I'm inclined to go the opposite direction: All of Active Support included all of the time! I don't have much interest in micromanaging the dependencies of Active Support for the frameworks within Rails. I think it's completely reasonable to say that any framework included in Rails is free to rely on any aspect of the Ruby dialect that is Active Support. And that any application that wish to use a Rails framework need to accept that this usage comes with an acceptance of this Ruby dialect."
      }
